Correlation Analysis For 2019

In [20]:
df19 = pd.DataFrame()
df19 = pd.concat([btc,eth,xrp,ltc,dash,xmr,rdd,vtc,ftc,nmc,blk,aur,nvc],join='outer',axis=1)

df19.columns.values[0] = 'DATE'
df19.columns.values[4] = 'btc'
df19.columns.values[11] = 'eth'
df19.columns.values[18] = 'xrp'
df19.columns.values[25] = 'ltc'
df19.columns.values[32] = 'dash'
df19.columns.values[39] = 'xmr'
df19.columns.values[46] = 'rdd'
df19.columns.values[53] = 'vtc'
df19.columns.values[60] = 'ftc'
df19.columns.values[67] = 'nmc'
df19.columns.values[74] = 'blk'
df19.columns.values[81] = 'aur'
df19.columns.values[88] = 'nvc'


df19 = df19.drop(['open', 'high', 'low','volume','marketcap','date'], axis=1)

df19.columns.values[0] = 'date'

start_date = '2019-01-01'
end_date = '2019-04-14'

# Apply the mask of the dates range set
mask = (df19['date'] > start_date) & (df19['date'] <= end_date)
df19 = df19.loc[mask]

df19 = df19.dropna()

pearson19 = df19.corr(method='pearson')
spearman19 = df19.corr(method='spearman')
kendall19 = df19.corr(method='kendall')

df17 = pd.DataFrame()
df17 = pd.concat([btc,eth,xrp,ltc,dash,xmr,rdd,vtc,ftc,nmc,blk,aur,nvc],join='outer',axis=1)

df17.columns.values[67] = 'nmc'

df17.columns.values[88] = 'nvc'
